   "source": [
    "# Numerical Summary Simulation with NumSummarySim\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Compute basic numerical summaries using **pure Python** utilities from `src.pure_python_stats`\n",
    "- Compute the same summaries using **NumPy** utilities from `src.numpy_stats`\n",
    "- Run simple **simulation experiments** using `src.simulation` to study sampling distributions\n",
    "- Visualize results with `src.utils.plotting_helpers`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up Python path so we can import from src when running directly from the repo root\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "repo_root = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), os.pardir)) if os.path.basename(os.getcwd()) == 'notebooks' else os.getcwd()\n",
    "src_path = os.path.join(repo_root, 'src')\n",
    "if src_path not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, src_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Repo root:', repo_root)\n",
    "print('Using src path:', src_path)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Imports from the project\n",
    "from pure_python_stats import mean, median, variance, std_dev, summary\n",
    "from numpy_stats import np_mean, np_median, np_variance, np_std, np_summary\n",
    "from simulation import run_statistic_simulation\n",
    "from utils.plotting_helpers import plot_histogram, plot_line_with_ci\n",
    "\n",
    "import random\n",
    "import numpy as np\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Basic numerical summaries (pure Python vs NumPy)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 10]\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Data:', data)\n",
    "print('Pure Python mean:', mean(data))\n",
    "print('NumPy mean:', np_mean(data))\n",
    "print('Pure Python median:', median(data))\n",
    "print('NumPy median:', np_median(data))\n",
    "print('Pure Python variance (ddof=1):', variance(data, ddof=1))\n",
    "print('NumPy variance (ddof=1):', np_variance(data, ddof=1))\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\nPure Python summary:')\n",
    "for k, v in summary(data).items():\n",
    "    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('\nNumPy summary:')\n",
    "for k, v in np_summary(data).items():\n",
    "    print(f'  {k}: {v}')\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation: Sampling distribution of the sample mean\n",
    "\n",
    "We will:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Draw many samples from a Normal(0, 1) distribution\n",
    "- Compute the sample mean for each simulation\n",
    "- Inspect the distribution of sample means\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fix seeds for reproducibility\n",
    "random.seed(42)\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "def normal_sample(n, mu=0.0, sigma=1.0):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Generate a random sample of size n from N(mu, sigma^2) using random.gauss.\"\"\"\n",
    "    return [random.gauss(mu, sigma) for _ in range(n)]\n",
    "\n",
    "sim_result = run_statistic_simulation(\n",
    "    sample_generator=lambda n: normal_sample(n, mu=0.0, sigma=1.0),\n",
    "    statistic=mean,\n",
    "    sample_size=30,\n",
    "    n_simulations=5000,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "sim_result.summary\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualize the sampling distribution of the mean\n",
    "plot_histogram(\n",
    "    sim_result.values,\n",
    "    bins=40,\n",
    "    title='Sampling Distribution of Sample Mean (Normal(0,1), n=30)',\n    "    xlabel='Sample mean',\n    "    ylabel='Frequency',\n    "    density=True,\n    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Exploring how sample size affects variability of the mean\n",
    "\n",
    "We repeat the experiment for several sample sizes and track the standard deviation of the simulated means.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sample_sizes = [5, 10, 30, 50, 100, 200]\n",
    "sd_of_means = []\n",
    "ci_lower = []\n",
    "ci_upper = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for n in sample_sizes:\n",
    "    result = run_statistic_simulation(\n",
    "        sample_generator=lambda k, n=n: normal_sample(k, mu=0.0, sigma=1.0),\n",
    "        statistic=mean,\n",
    "        sample_size=n,\n",
    "        n_simulations=3000,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    sd_of_means.append(result.summary['std'])\n",
    "    ci_lower.append(result.summary['q2.5'])\n",
    "    ci_upper.append(result.summary['q97.5'])\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_line_with_ci(\n",
    "    x=sample_sizes,\n",
    "    y=sd_of_means,\n",
    "    y_lower=None,\n",
    "    y_upper=None,\n",
    "    title='Standard Deviation of Sample Mean vs Sample Size',\n",
    "    xlabel='Sample size',\n",
    "    ylabel='Std dev of sample mean',\n",
    "    x_log=True,\n",
    ")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
